  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Purpose: To investigate the relationship between retinal thickness (RT) and metabolic risks
      (MRs) in patients without retinal lesion.

      Methods: Fifty-two patients over 60 y/o were divided into four groups according to their MRs
      of hypertension, hyperlipidemia or hyperglyceremia. After complete ophthalmic examination,
      optical coherence tomography was performed to measure RT.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
