    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  We enrolled the patients included age more than 60 years old, no positive finding
             during dilated fundus examination.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  The exclusion criteria were as followed:

               -  systemic disease that will affect visual acuity evaluation (for example: CVA),
                  *opaque cornea and vitreous

               -  glaucoma

               -  uvietis and other clinically established ocular disease.

          -  According to the LOCS III11, those who had nuclear opalescence, nuclear color more
             than grade 3 or any grade of cortical cataract and posterior subcapsular cataract were
             also eliminated.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
